swEgressAclMgmtMIB.name: swEgressAclMgmtMIB
swEgressAclMgmtMIB.description: The structure of Egress Access Control List information for the proprietary enterprise.

swEgressACLTotalUsedRuleEntries.name: swEgressACLTotalUsedRuleEntries
swEgressACLTotalUsedRuleEntries.description: The total number of used egress ACL rule entries.

swEgressACLTotalUnusedRuleEntries.name: swEgressACLTotalUnusedRuleEntries
swEgressACLTotalUnusedRuleEntries.description: The total number of unused egress ACL rule entries.

swEgressACLEthernetTable.name: swEgressACLEthernetTable
swEgressACLEthernetTable.description: This table contains egress ACL mask Ethernet information. The access profile will be created on the switch to define which part of each outgoing frame's layer 2 header will be examined by the switch. Masks entered will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swEgressACLEthernetEntry.name: swEgressACLEthernetEntry
swEgressACLEthernetEntry.description: A list of information about the egress ACL for Ethernet.

swEgressACLEthernetProfileID.name: swEgressACLEthernetProfileID
swEgressACLEthernetProfileID.description: The ID of the egress ACL mask entry unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swEgressACLEthernetRowStatus.name: swEgressACLEthernetRowStatus
swEgressACLEthernetRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swEgressACLEthernetProfileName.name: swEgressACLEthernetProfileName
swEgressACLEthernetProfileName.description: The name of the egress ACL mask entry unique to the mask list.

swEgressACLEthernetUsevlan.name: swEgressACLEthernetUsevlan
swEgressACLEthernetUsevlan.description: Specifies that the switch will examine the VLAN part of each packet header.

swEgressACLEthernetVlanMask.name: swEgressACLEthernetVlanMask
swEgressACLEthernetVlanMask.description: The mask used for the VLAN ID. Valid values are from 0x0000 to 0x0FFF. The default value is 0x0FFF

swEgressACLEthernetUse8021p.name: swEgressACLEthernetUse8021p
swEgressACLEthernetUse8021p.description: Specifies if the switch will examine the 802.1p priority value in the frame's header or not.

swEgressACLEthernetUseEthernetType.name: swEgressACLEthernetUseEthernetType
swEgressACLEthernetUseEthernetType.description: Specifies if the switch will examine the Ethernet type value in each frame's header or not.

swEgressACLEthernetMacAddrMaskState.name: swEgressACLEthernetMacAddrMaskState
swEgressACLEthernetMacAddrMaskState.description: This object indicates the status of the MAC address mask. other (1) - Neither source MAC address nor destination MAC address is masked. dst-mac-addr (2) - Destination MAC addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the MAC address entry for the table. src-mac-addr (3) - Source MAC addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the MAC address entry for the table. dst-src-mac-addr (4) - Source or destination MAC addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the MAC address entry of the table.

swEgressACLEthernetSrcMacAddrMask.name: swEgressACLEthernetSrcMacAddrMask
swEgressACLEthernetSrcMacAddrMask.description: This object specifies the MAC address mask for the source MAC address.

swEgressACLEthernetDstMacAddrMask.name: swEgressACLEthernetDstMacAddrMask
swEgressACLEthernetDstMacAddrMask.description: This object specifies the MAC address mask for the destination MAC address.

swEgressACLEthernetUnusedRuleEntries.name: swEgressACLEthernetUnusedRuleEntries
swEgressACLEthernetUnusedRuleEntries.description: The number of unused rule entries of this Ethernet profile entry.

swEgressACLIpTable.name: swEgressACLIpTable
swEgressACLIpTable.description: This table contains the egress ACL mask for IP information. Access profiles will be created on the switch to define which part of the outgoing frame's IP layer packet header will be examined by the switch. Masks entered will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swEgressACLIpEntry.name: swEgressACLIpEntry
swEgressACLIpEntry.description: A list of information about the egress ACL of the IP layer.

swEgressACLIpProfileID.name: swEgressACLIpProfileID
swEgressACLIpProfileID.description: The ID of the egress ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swEgressACLIpRowStatus.name: swEgressACLIpRowStatus
swEgressACLIpRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swEgressACLIpProfileName.name: swEgressACLIpProfileName
swEgressACLIpProfileName.description: The name of the egress ACL mask entry unique to the mask list.

swEgressACLIpUsevlan.name: swEgressACLIpUsevlan
swEgressACLIpUsevlan.description: This object indicates if the IP layer VLAN part is examined or not.

swEgressACLIpVlanMask.name: swEgressACLIpVlanMask
swEgressACLIpVlanMask.description: The mask used for the VLAN ID. Valid values are from 0x0000 to 0x0FFF. The default value is 0x0FFF.

swEgressACLIpIpAddrMaskState.name: swEgressACLIpIpAddrMaskState
swEgressACLIpIpAddrMaskState.description: This object indicates the status of IP address mask. other (1) - Neither source IP address nor destination IP address is masked. dst-ip-addr (2) - Destination IP addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the IP address entry of the table. src-ip-addr (3) - Source IP addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the IP address entry of the table. dst-src-ip-addr (4) - Destination or source IP addresses within received frames are to be filtered when matched with the IP address entry of the table.

swEgressACLIpSrcIpAddrMask.name: swEgressACLIpSrcIpAddrMask
swEgressACLIpSrcIpAddrMask.description: This object specifies the IP address mask for the source IP address.

swEgressACLIpDstIpAddrMask.name: swEgressACLIpDstIpAddrMask
swEgressACLIpDstIpAddrMask.description: This object specifies the IP address mask for the destination IP address.

swEgressACLIpUseDSCP.name: swEgressACLIpUseDSCP
swEgressACLIpUseDSCP.description: This object indicates if the DSCP protocol in the packet header is to be examined or not.

swEgressACLIpUseProtoType.name: swEgressACLIpUseProtoType
swEgressACLIpUseProtoType.description: That object indicates which protocol will be examined.

swEgressACLIpIcmpOption.name: swEgressACLIpIcmpOption
swEgressACLIpIcmpOption.description: This object indicates which fields are defined for ICMP. none (1)- Both fields are null. type (2)- Type field identified. code (3)- Code field identified. type-code (4)- Both ICMP fields identified.

swEgressACLIpIgmpOption.name: swEgressACLIpIgmpOption
swEgressACLIpIgmpOption.description: Indicates if the IGMP options field is identified or not.

swEgressACLIpTcpOption.name: swEgressACLIpTcpOption
swEgressACLIpTcpOption.description: This object indicates the status of the filtered address of TCP. other (1) - Neither source port nor destination port is masked. dst-addr (2) - Packets will be filtered if this destination port is identified in received frames. src-addr (3) - Packets will be filtered if this source port is identified in received frames. dst-src-addr (4) - Packets will be filtered if this destination or source port is identified in received frames.

swEgressACLIpUdpOption.name: swEgressACLIpUdpOption
swEgressACLIpUdpOption.description: This object indicates the status of the filtered address of UDP . other (1) - Neither source port nor destination port is masked. dst-addr (2) - Packets will be filtered if this destination port is identified in received frames. src-addr (3) - Packets will be filtered if this source port is identified in received frames. dst-src-addr (4) - Packets will be filtered if this destination or source port is identified in received frames.

swEgressACLIpTCPorUDPSrcPortMask.name: swEgressACLIpTCPorUDPSrcPortMask
swEgressACLIpTCPorUDPSrcPortMask.description: Specifies a TCP port mask for the source port if swEgressACLIpUseProtoType is TCP Specifies a UDP port mask for the source port if swEgressACLIpUseProtoType is UDP.

swEgressACLIpTCPorUDPDstPortMask.name: swEgressACLIpTCPorUDPDstPortMask
swEgressACLIpTCPorUDPDstPortMask.description: Specifies a TCP port mask for the destination port if swEgressACLIpUseProtoType is TCP Specifies a UDP port mask for the destination port if swEgressACLIpUseProtoType is UDP.

swEgressACLIpTCPFlagBit.name: swEgressACLIpTCPFlagBit
swEgressACLIpTCPFlagBit.description: Specifies a TCP connection flag mask.

swEgressACLIpTCPFlagBitMask.name: swEgressACLIpTCPFlagBitMask
swEgressACLIpTCPFlagBitMask.description: A value which indicates the set of TCP flags that this entity may potentially offer. The value is a sum of flag bits. This sum initially takes the value zero. Then, for each flag, L, is added in the range 1 through 6, for which this node performs transactions where 2^(L-1) is added to the sum. Note that values should be calculated accordingly: Flag functionality 6 urg bit 5 ack bit 4 psh bit 3 rst bit 2 syn bit 1 fin bit For example, if you want to enable urg bit and ack bit, you should set value 48{2^(5-1) + 2^(6-1)}.

swEgressACLIpProtoIDOption.name: swEgressACLIpProtoIDOption
swEgressACLIpProtoIDOption.description: Specifies if the switch will examine each frame's protocol ID field or not.

swEgressACLIpProtoID.name: swEgressACLIpProtoID
swEgressACLIpProtoID.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IP protocol ID behind the IP header.

swEgressACLIpProtoIDMask.name: swEgressACLIpProtoIDMask
swEgressACLIpProtoIDMask.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IP protocol ID and the mask options behind the IP header.

swEgressACLIpUnusedRuleEntries.name: swEgressACLIpUnusedRuleEntries
swEgressACLIpUnusedRuleEntries.description: The number of unused rule entries this IP profile entry.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskTable.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskTable
swEgressACLIpv6MaskTable.description: This table contains IPv6 egress ACL mask information. An access profile will be created on the switch to define which parts of each outgoing frame's IPv6 part of the packet header will be examined by the switch. Masks entered will be combined with the values the switch finds in the specified frame header fields.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskEntry.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskEntry
swEgressACLIpv6MaskEntry.description: A list of information about egress ACL for IPv6.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskProfileID.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskProfileID
swEgressACLIpv6MaskProfileID.description: The ID of the egress ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskRowStatus.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskRowStatus
swEgressACLIpv6MaskRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskProfileName.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskProfileName
swEgressACLIpv6MaskProfileName.description: The name of egress ACL mask entry unique to the mask list.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskClass.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskClass
swEgressACLIpv6MaskClass.description: This object indicates if the class field in the IPv6 packet header is to be examined or not.

swEgressACLIpv6IpAddrMaskState.name: swEgressACLIpv6IpAddrMaskState
swEgressACLIpv6IpAddrMaskState.description: This object indicates the status of the IPv6 address mask. other (1) - Neither source IPv6 address nor destination IPv6 address is masked. dst-ipv6-addr (2) - Received frame destination IPv6 address is currently used to be filtered as it meets with the IPv6 address entry of the table. src-ipv6-addr (3) - Received frame source IPv6 address is currently used to be filtered as it meets with the IPv6 address entry of the table. dst-src-ipv6-addr (4) - Received frame destination IPv6 address or source IPv6 address is currently used to be filtered as it meets with the IPv6 address entry of the table.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskSrcIpv6Mask.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskSrcIpv6Mask
swEgressACLIpv6MaskSrcIpv6Mask.description: This object specifies the IPv6 address mask for the source IPv6 address.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskDstIpv6Mask.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskDstIpv6Mask
swEgressACLIpv6MaskDstIpv6Mask.description: This object specifies the IPv6 address mask for the destination IPv6 address.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType
swEgressACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType.description: That object indicates which protocol will be examined.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskIcmpOption.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskIcmpOption
swEgressACLIpv6MaskIcmpOption.description: This object indicates which fields are defined for ICMP. none (1)- Both fields are null. type (2)- Type field identified. code (3)- Code field identified. type-code (4)- Both ICMP fields identified.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskTcpOption.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskTcpOption
swEgressACLIpv6MaskTcpOption.description: This object indicates the status of the filtered address of TCP. other (1) - Neither source port nor destination port is masked. dst-addr (2) - Packets will be filtered if this destination port is identified in received frames. src-addr (3) - Packets will be filtered if this source port is identified in received frames. dst-src-addr (4) - Packets will be filtered if this destination or source port is identified in received frames.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskUdpOption.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskUdpOption
swEgressACLIpv6MaskUdpOption.description: This object indicates the status of the filtered address of UDP. other (1) - Neither source port nor destination port is masked. dst-addr (2) - Packets will be filtered if this destination port is identified in received frames. src-addr (3) - Packets will be filtered if this source port is identified in received frames. dst-src-addr (4) - Packets will be filtered if this destination or source port is identified in received frames.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskTCPorUDPSrcPortMask.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskTCPorUDPSrcPortMask
swEgressACLIpv6MaskTCPorUDPSrcPortMask.description: Specifies a TCP port mask for the source port if swEgressACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType is TCP Specifies a UDP port mask for the source port if swEgressACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType is UDP.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskTCPorUDPDstPortMask.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskTCPorUDPDstPortMask
swEgressACLIpv6MaskTCPorUDPDstPortMask.description: Specifies a TCP port mask for the destination port if swEgressACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType is TCP Specifies a UDP port mask for the destination port if swEgressACLIpv6MaskUseProtoType is UDP.

swEgressACLIpv6MaskUnusedRuleEntries.name: swEgressACLIpv6MaskUnusedRuleEntries
swEgressACLIpv6MaskUnusedRuleEntries.description: The number of unused rule entries of this IPv6 profile entry.

swEgressACLMaskDelAllState.name: swEgressACLMaskDelAllState
swEgressACLMaskDelAllState.description: Used to delete all egress ACL masks.

swEgressACLEtherRuleTable.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleTable
swEgressACLEtherRuleTable.description: This table contains Ethernet egress ACL information.

swEgressACLEtherRuleEntry.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleEntry
swEgressACLEtherRuleEntry.description: A list of information about the egress ACL rule of the layer 2 part of each packet.

swEgressACLEtherRuleProfileID.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleProfileID
swEgressACLEtherRuleProfileID.description: The ID of the egress ACL rule entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swEgressACLEtherRuleAccessID.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleAccessID
swEgressACLEtherRuleAccessID.description: The ID of the the egress ACL rule entry relates to the swEgressACLEtherRuleProfileID. When row creation is set to 0, this indicates the access ID will be assigned automatically. When set from 1 to 65535, an access ID will be created for the rule.

swEgressACLEtherRuleRowStatus.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleRowStatus
swEgressACLEtherRuleRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swEgressACLEtherRuleMatchVID.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleMatchVID
swEgressACLEtherRuleMatchVID.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply only to packets with this VLAN ID. It is applied to the specified ports configured by swEgressACLEtherRulePortGroup. Note:A value of 0 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLEtherRuleMatchVlanMask.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleMatchVlanMask
swEgressACLEtherRuleMatchVlanMask.description: Specifies the per rule mask for the VLAN field as defined in swEgressACLEtherRuleVlan object. The value of this object when not in use is the corresponding mask in the profile mask. Once the value of this object is modified, the per rule mask will take effect.

swEgressACLEtherRuleSrcMacAddress.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleSrcMacAddress
swEgressACLEtherRuleSrcMacAddress.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply to only packets with this source MAC address.

swEgressACLEtherRuleMaskSrcMacAddress.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleMaskSrcMacAddress
swEgressACLEtherRuleMaskSrcMacAddress.description: Specifies the per rule mask for the source MAC addres field as defined in swEgressACLEtherRuleSrcMacAddress object. The value of this object when not in use is the corresponding mask in the profile mask. Once the value of this object is modified, the per rule mask will take effect.

swEgressACLEtherRuleDstMacAddress.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleDstMacAddress
swEgressACLEtherRuleDstMacAddress.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply to packets with this destination MAC address.

swEgressACLEtherRuleMaskDstMacAddress.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleMaskDstMacAddress
swEgressACLEtherRuleMaskDstMacAddress.description: Specifies the per rule mask for the destination MAC addres field as defined in swEgressACLEtherRuleDstMacAddress object. The value of this object when not in use is the corresponding mask in the profile mask. Once the value of this object is modified, the per rule mask will take effect.

swEgressACLEtherRule8021P.name: swEgressACLEtherRule8021P
swEgressACLEtherRule8021P.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply to packets with this 802.1p priority value. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLEtherRuleEtherType.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleEtherType
swEgressACLEtherRuleEtherType.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply to packets with this hexadecimal 802.1Q Ethernet type value in the packet header.

swEgressACLEtherRuleVID.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleVID
swEgressACLEtherRuleVID.description: Specifies the VLAN-based ACL rule. There are two conditions: 1. this rule will apply to all the ports; 2. packets must belong to this VLAN. This object and swEgressACLEtherRulePortGroup,swEgressACLEtherRulePort cannot be set together. When you set swEgressACLEtherRulePortGroup or swEgressACLEtherRulePort, the value of this object will change to 0 automatically. This object cannot be set to 0.

swEgressACLEtherRulePort.name: swEgressACLEtherRulePort
swEgressACLEtherRulePort.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to the port. This object and swEgressACLEtherRuleVID,swEgressACLEtherRulePortGroup can not be set together. When you set swEgressACLEtherRuleVID or swEgressACLEtherRulePortGroup, the value of this object will change to 0 automatically. This object can not be set to 0. A value of 0 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLEtherRulePortGroup.name: swEgressACLEtherRulePortGroup
swEgressACLEtherRulePortGroup.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to port(s) which belong to this port group. This object and swEgressACLEtherRuleVID, swEgressACLEtherRulePort can not be set together.When you set swEgressACLEtherRuleVID or swEgressACLEtherRulePort the value of this object will change to 0 automatically. Note:The range of this object is (0..N). The value N means the max number. It is determined by the project itself.A value of 0 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLEtherRulePermit.name: swEgressACLEtherRulePermit
swEgressACLEtherRulePermit.description: This object indicates if the result of the packet examination is 'permit' or 'deny'. The default is 'permit'. deny - Specifies that packets matching the access profile are not permitted to be forwarded by the switch and will be filtered. permit - Specifies that packets matching the access profile are permitted to be forwarded by the switch.

swEgressACLEtherRuleEnableReplacePriorit.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleEnableReplacePriority
swEgressACLEtherRuleEnableReplacePriorit.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile 802.1p priority tag field or not .

swEgressACLEtherRuleReplacePriority.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleReplacePriority
swEgressACLEtherRuleReplacePriority.description: Specifies that the priority will be changed in packets while the swEgressACLEtherRuleEnablePriority is enabled.A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLEtherRuleEnableReplaceDscp.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleEnableReplaceDscp
swEgressACLEtherRuleEnableReplaceDscp.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile DSCP field or not.

swEgressACLEtherRuleReplaceDscp.name: swEgressACLEtherRuleReplaceDscp
swEgressACLEtherRuleReplaceDscp.description: Specifies a value to be written to the DSCP field of an outgoing packet that meets the criteria specified in the first part of the command. This value will over-write the value in the DSCP field of the packet. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressAclEtherRuleTimeRangeName.name: swEgressAclEtherRuleTimeRangeName
swEgressAclEtherRuleTimeRangeName.description: Specifies a name of a time-range associated with a specific egress ACL entry. The time-range name must first be created before being associated with the access rule. If this name is an empty string, the time-range profile will no longer be associated with the access rule. When a rule is de-associated with a time range, the access rule will be enabled all the time.

swEgressACLIpRuleProfileID.name: swEgressACLIpRuleProfileID
swEgressACLIpRuleProfileID.description: The ID of the egress ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swEgressACLIpRuleAccessID.name: swEgressACLIpRuleAccessID
swEgressACLIpRuleAccessID.description: The ID of the egress ACL rule entry relates to the swEgressACLEtherRuleProfileID. When row creation is set to 0, this indicates the access ID will be assigned automatically. When set from 1 to 65535, an access ID will be created for the rule.

swEgressACLIpRuleRowStatus.name: swEgressACLIpRuleRowStatus
swEgressACLIpRuleRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swEgressACLIpRuleMatchVID.name: swEgressACLIpRuleMatchVID
swEgressACLIpRuleMatchVID.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply only to packets with this VLAN ID. It is applied to the specified ports configured by swEgressACLIpRulePortGroup. Note:A value of 0 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpMatchVlanMask.name: swEgressACLIpMatchVlanMask
swEgressACLIpMatchVlanMask.description: Specifies the per rule mask for the VLAN as defined in swEgressACLIpRuleVlan object. The value of this object when not in use is the corresponding mask in the profile mask. Once the value of this object is modified, the per rule mask will take effect. This object is writeable only once.

swEgressACLIpRuleMaskSrcIpaddress.name: swEgressACLIpRuleMaskSrcIpaddress
swEgressACLIpRuleMaskSrcIpaddress.description: Specifies the per rule mask for the source IP address as defined in swEgressACLIpRuleSrcIpaddress object. The value of this object when not in use is the corresponding mask in the profile mask. Once the value of this object is modified, the per rule mask will take effect. This object is writeable only once.

swEgressACLIpRuleMaskDstIpaddress.name: swEgressACLIpRuleMaskDstIpaddress
swEgressACLIpRuleMaskDstIpaddress.description: Specifies the per rule mask for the destination IP address as defined in swEgressACLIpRuleMaskDstIpaddress object. The value of this object when not in use is the corresponding mask in the profile mask. Once the value of this object is modified, the per rule mask will take effect. This object is writeable only once.

swEgressACLIpRuleDscp.name: swEgressACLIpRuleDscp
swEgressACLIpRuleDscp.description: Specifies the value of DSCP. The value can be configured from 0 to 63. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpRuleType.name: swEgressACLIpRuleType
swEgressACLIpRuleType.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the value of ICMP/IGMP type traffic. A value of -1 denotes that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpRuleCode.name: swEgressACLIpRuleCode
swEgressACLIpRuleCode.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the value of ICMP code traffic. A value of -1 denotes that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpRuleSrcPort.name: swEgressACLIpRuleSrcPort
swEgressACLIpRuleSrcPort.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the range of the TCP/UDP source ports. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpRuleMaskSrcPort.name: swEgressACLIpRuleMaskSrcPort
swEgressACLIpRuleMaskSrcPort.description: Specifies the per rule mask for the L4 source port as defined in swEgressACLIpRuleSrcPort object. The value of this object when not in use is the corresponding mask in the profile mask. Once the value of this object is modified, the per rule mask will take effect. This object is writeable only once.

swEgressACLIpRuleDstPort.name: swEgressACLIpRuleDstPort
swEgressACLIpRuleDstPort.description: Specifies the TCP/UDP destination port range. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpRuleMaskDstPort.name: swEgressACLIpRuleMaskDstPort
swEgressACLIpRuleMaskDstPort.description: Specifies the per rule mask for the L4 destination port as defined in swEgressACLIpRuleDstPort object. The value of this object when not in use is the corresponding mask in the profile mask. Once the value of this object is modified, the per rule mask will take effect. This object is writeable only once.

swEgressACLIpRuleFlagBits.name: swEgressACLIpRuleFlagBits
swEgressACLIpRuleFlagBits.description: A value which indicates the set of TCP flags that this entity may potentially offer. The value is a sum of flag bits. This sum initially takes the value zero. Then, for each flag, L is added in the range 1 through 6, for which this node performs transactions, where 2^(L - 1) is added to the sum. Note that values should be calculated accordingly: Flag functionality 6 urg bit 5 ack bit 4 psh bit 3 rst bit 2 syn bit 1 fin bit For example, it you want to enable urg bit and ack bit, you should set value 48{2^(5-1) + 2^(6-1)}.

swEgressACLIpRuleProtoID.name: swEgressACLIpRuleProtoID
swEgressACLIpRuleProtoID.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the value of IP protocol ID traffic. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpRuleUserDefine.name: swEgressACLIpRuleUserDefine
swEgressACLIpRuleUserDefine.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the first four byte behind the IP header.

swEgressACLIpRuleUserDefineMask.name: swEgressACLIpRuleUserDefineMask
swEgressACLIpRuleUserDefineMask.description: Specifies the per rule mask for the first four byte behind the IP header as defined in swEgressACLIpRuleUserDefine object.

swEgressACLIpRuleVID.name: swEgressACLIpRuleVID
swEgressACLIpRuleVID.description: Specifies the VLAN-based rule. There are two conditions: 1. this rule will apply to all the ports; 2. packets must belong to this VLAN. This object and swEgressACLIpRulePortGroup,swEgressACLIpRulePort cannot be set together. When you set swEgressACLIpRulePortGroup or swEgressACLIpRulePort , the value of this object will change to 0 automatically. This object cannot be set 0.

swEgressACLIpRulePort.name: swEgressACLIpRulePort
swEgressACLIpRulePort.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to the port. This object and swEgressACLIpRuleVID,swEgressACLIpRulePortGroup can not be set together.When you set swEgressACLIpRuleVID or swEgressACLIpRulePortGroup, the value of this object will change to 0 automatically. This object can not be set to 0. A value of 0 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpRulePortGroup.name: swEgressACLIpRulePortGroup
swEgressACLIpRulePortGroup.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to port(s)which belong to this port group. This object and swEgressACLIpRuleVID,swEgressACLIpRulePort can not be set together. When you set swEgressACLIpRuleVID or swEgressACLIpRulePort , the value of this object will change to 0 automatically. Note:The range of this object is (0..N).The value N means the max number.It is determined by the project itself. A value of 0 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpRulePermit.name: swEgressACLIpRulePermit
swEgressACLIpRulePermit.description: This object indicates if the result of the packet examination is 'permit' or 'deny'. The default is 'permit'. deny - Specifies that packets matching the access profile are not permitted to be forwarded by the switch and will be filtered. permit - Specifies that packets matching the access profile are permitted to be forwarded by the switch.

swEgressACLIpRuleEnableReplacePriority.name: swEgressACLIpRuleEnableReplacePriority
swEgressACLIpRuleEnableReplacePriority.description: Specifies whether the packets that match the access profile will change the 802.1p priority tag field by the switch or not.

swEgressACLIpRuleReplacePriority.name: swEgressACLIpRuleReplacePriority
swEgressACLIpRuleReplacePriority.description: Specifies the priority will change in packets while the swEgressACLIpRuleEnablePriority is enabled.A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpRuleEnableReplaceDscp.name: swEgressACLIpRuleEnableReplaceDscp
swEgressACLIpRuleEnableReplaceDscp.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile DSCP field or not.

swEgressACLIpRuleReplaceDscp.name: swEgressACLIpRuleReplaceDscp
swEgressACLIpRuleReplaceDscp.description: Specifies a value to be written to the DSCP field of an outgoing packet that meets the criteria specified in the first part of the command. This value will over-write the value in the DSCP field of the packet. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressAclIpRuleTimeRangeName.name: swEgressAclIpRuleTimeRangeName
swEgressAclIpRuleTimeRangeName.description: Specifies a name of a time-range associated with a specific egress ACL entry. The time-range name must first be created before being associated with the access rule. If this name is an empty string, the time-range profile will no longer be associated with the access rule. When a rule is de-associated with a time range, the access rule will be enabled all the time.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleTable.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleTable
swEgressACLIpv6RuleTable.description: This table contains the IPv6 egress ACL rule information.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleEntry.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleEntry
swEgressACLIpv6RuleEntry.description: A list of information about egress ACL rules regarding the IPv6 part of each packet.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleProfileID.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleProfileID
swEgressACLIpv6RuleProfileID.description: The ID of the egress ACL mask entry, which is unique to the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleAccessID.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleAccessID
swEgressACLIpv6RuleAccessID.description: The ID of the the egress ACL rule entry relates to the swEgressACLEtherRuleProfileID. When row creation is set to 0, this indicates the access ID will be assigned automatically. When set from 1 to 65535, an access ID will be created for the rule.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleRowStatus.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleRowStatus
swEgressACLIpv6RuleRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleClass.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleClass
swEgressACLIpv6RuleClass.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the IPv6 class field. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleSrcIpv6Addr.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleSrcIpv6Addr
swEgressACLIpv6RuleSrcIpv6Addr.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the source IPv6 address.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleMaskSrcIpv6Addr.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleMaskSrcIpv6Addr
swEgressACLIpv6RuleMaskSrcIpv6Addr.description: Specifies that the per rule mask of swEgressACLIpv6RuleSrcIpv6Addr. The value of this object when not in use is the corresponding mask in the profile mask. Once the value of this object is modified, the per rule mask will take effect. This object is writeable only once.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleDstIpv6Addr.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleDstIpv6Addr
swEgressACLIpv6RuleDstIpv6Addr.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the destination IPv6 address.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleMaskDstIpv6Addr.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleMaskDstIpv6Addr
swEgressACLIpv6RuleMaskDstIpv6Addr.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the destination IPv6 address.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleType.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleType
swEgressACLIpv6RuleType.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the value of ICMP type traffic. A value of -1 denotes that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleCode.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleCode
swEgressACLIpv6RuleCode.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the value of ICMP code traffic. A value of -1 denotes that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleSrcPort.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleSrcPort
swEgressACLIpv6RuleSrcPort.description: Specifies that the rule applies to the range of the TCP/UDP source ports. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleMaskSrcPort.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleMaskSrcPort
swEgressACLIpv6RuleMaskSrcPort.description: Specifies that the per rule mask of swEgressACLIpv6RuleSrcPort. The value of this object when not in use is the corresponding mask in the profile mask. Once the value of this object is modified, the per rule mask will take effect. This object is writeable only once.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleDstPort.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleDstPort
swEgressACLIpv6RuleDstPort.description: Specifies the TCP/UDP destination port range. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleMaskDstPort.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleMaskDstPort
swEgressACLIpv6RuleMaskDstPort.description: Specifies the per rule mask of swEgressACLIpv6RuleDstPort. The value of this object when not in use is the corresponding mask in the profile mask. Once the value of this object is modified, the per rule mask will take effect. This object is writeable only once.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleVID.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleVID
swEgressACLIpv6RuleVID.description: Specifies this rule only applies to the specified VLAN. There are two conditions: 1.only the portlist that belongs to this VLAN will be included; 2.packets must belong to this VLAN. This object and swEgressACLIpv6RulePortGroup,swEgressACLIpv6RulePort cannot be set together. When you set swEgressACLIpv6RulePortGroup or swEgressACLIpv6RulePort, the value of this object will change to 0 automatically. The object cannot be set 0.

swEgressACLIpv6RulePort.name: swEgressACLIpv6RulePort
swEgressACLIpv6RulePort.description: Specifies that the access rule will only apply to the port. This object and swEgressACLIpv6RuleVID,swEgressACLIpv6RulePortGroup can not be set together.When you set swEgressACLIpv6RuleVID or swEgressACLIpv6RulePortGroup, the value of this object will change to 0 automatically. This object can not be set to 0. A value of 0 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpv6RulePortGroup.name: swEgressACLIpv6RulePortGroup
swEgressACLIpv6RulePortGroup.description: Specifies that the access rule will apply only to port(s)which belong to this port group. This object and swEgressACLIpv6RuleVID,swEgressACLIpv6RulePort can not be set together. When you set swEgressACLIpv6RuleVID or swEgressACLIpv6RulePort, the value of this object will change to 0 automatically. Note:The range of this object is (0..N).The value N means the max number.It is determined by the project itself.A value of 0 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpv6RulePermit.name: swEgressACLIpv6RulePermit

The default is 'permit'. deny - Specifies that packets matching the access profile are not permitted to be forwarded by the switch and will be filtered. permit - Specifies that packets matching the access profile are permitted to be forwarded by the switch.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleEnableReplacePriority.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleEnableReplacePriority
swEgressACLIpv6RuleEnableReplacePriority.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile 802.1p priority tag or not.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleReplacePriority.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleReplacePriority
swEgressACLIpv6RuleReplacePriority.description: Specifies the priority will change in packets while the swEgressACLIpv6RuleReplacePriority is enabled.A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleEnableReplaceDscp.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleEnableReplaceDscp
swEgressACLIpv6RuleEnableReplaceDscp.description: Specifies if the switch will change priorities of packets that match the access profile DSCP field or not.

swEgressACLIpv6RuleReplaceDscp.name: swEgressACLIpv6RuleReplaceDscp
swEgressACLIpv6RuleReplaceDscp.description: Specifies a value to be written to the DSCP field of an outgoing packet that meets the criteria specified in the first part of the command. This value will over-write the value in the DSCP field of the packet. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressAclIpv6RuleTimeRangeName.name: swEgressAclIpv6RuleTimeRangeName
swEgressAclIpv6RuleTimeRangeName.description: Specifies a name of a time-range associated with a specific egress ACL entry. The time-range name must first be created before being associated with the access rule. If this name is an empty string, the time-range profile will no longer be associated with the access rule. When a rule is de-associated with a time range, the access rule will be enabled all the time.

swEgressACLCounterTable.name: swEgressACLCounterTable
swEgressACLCounterTable.description: This table maintains counter information associated with a specific rule in the egress ACL rule table. Please refer to the swEgressACLEtherRuleTable, swEgressACLIpRuleTable, swEgressACLIpv6RuleTable for detailed ACL rule information.

swEgressACLCounterEntry.name: swEgressACLCounterEntry
swEgressACLCounterEntry.description: The entry maintains counter information associated with the egress ACL rule table.

swEgressACLCounterProfileID.name: swEgressACLCounterProfileID
swEgressACLCounterProfileID.description: The ID of the egress ACL mask entry, which is unique in the mask list.

swEgressACLCounterAccessID.name: swEgressACLCounterAccessID
swEgressACLCounterAccessID.description: The ID of the egress ACL rule entry as related to the swEgressACLCounterProfileID.

swEgressACLCounterState.name: swEgressACLCounterState
swEgressACLCounterState.description: Specifies whether the counter feature will be enabled or disabled. 1. This is optional. The default is 'disabled'. 2. If the rule is not bound with flow-meter, then all packets that match will be counted. If the rule is bound with flow-meter, then the 'counter' will be overridden.

swEgressACLCounterGreenCounter.name: swEgressACLCounterGreenCounter
swEgressACLCounterGreenCounter.description: The number of matched green packets.

swEgressACLCounterYellowCounter.name: swEgressACLCounterYellowCounter
swEgressACLCounterYellowCounter.description: The number of matched yellow packets.

swEgressACLCounterRedCounter.name: swEgressACLCounterRedCounter
swEgressACLCounterRedCounter.description: The number of matched red packets.

swEgressAclMeterTable.name: swEgressAclMeterTable
swEgressAclMeterTable.description: This table is used to configure the flow-based metering function. The access rule must first be created before the parameters of this function can be applied. Users may set the preferred bandwidth for this rule, in Kbps; once the bandwidth has been exceeded, overflow packets will be either dropped or set for a drop precedence, depending on user configuration.

swEgressAclMeterEntry.name: swEgressAclMeterEntry
swEgressAclMeterEntry.description: This entry displays parameters and configurations set for the flow metering function.

swEgressAclMeterProfileID.name: swEgressAclMeterProfileID
swEgressAclMeterProfileID.description: The ID of the ACL mask entry is unique in the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swEgressAclMeterAccessID.name: swEgressAclMeterAccessID
swEgressAclMeterAccessID.description: The ID of the egress ACL rule entry as related to the swEgressAclMeterProfileID.

swEgressAclMeterRowStatus.name: swEgressAclMeterRowStatus
swEgressAclMeterRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swEgressAclMeterMode.name: swEgressAclMeterMode
swEgressAclMeterMode.description: tr-tcm: two rate three color mode; sr-tcm: single rate three color mode;

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmCir.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmCir
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmCir.description: Specifies the 'committed information rate' of 'two rate three color mode'. The unit is Kbps.A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmCbs.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmCbs
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmCbs.description: Specifies the 'committed burst size' of 'two rate three color mode'. 1. The unit is Kbytes. That is to say, 1 means 1Kbytes. 2. This parameter is an optional parameter. The default value is 4kbytes. Note:The set value range is 0..N. The value N is determined by project. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmPir.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmPir
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmPir.description: Specifies the 'Peak Information Rate' of 'two rate three color mode'. The unit is Kbps.A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmPbs.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmPbs
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmPbs.description: Specifies the 'peak burst size' of 'two rate three color mode'. 1. The unit is Kbytes. That is to say, 1 means 1kbytes. 2. This parameter is an optional parameter. The default value is 4kbytes. Note:The set value range is 0..N.The value N is determined by project. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmColorMode.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmColorMode
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmColorMode.description: Specifies the meter mode. The default is color-blind mode. The final color of the packet is determined by the initial color of the packet and the metering result.

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmConformState.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmConformState
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmConformState.description: Specifies the action state when packet is in 'green color'. permit: permit the packet. replace-dscp: change the DSCP value of packet.

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmConformReplaceDscp.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmConformReplaceDscp
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmConformReplaceDscp.description: Specifies the DSCP value of the packet when the packet is in 'green color'. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmConformCounterState.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmConformCounterState
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmConformCounterState.description: Specifies the counter state when the packet is in 'green color'. 1. This is optional. The default is 'disabled'. 2. The resource may be limited so that the counter cannot be turned on. The limitation is project dependent. 3. counter will be cleared when the function is disabled.

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmExceedState.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmExceedState
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmExceedState.description: Specifies the action state when packet is in 'yellow color'. permit: permit the packet. replace-dscp: change the DSCP value of the packet. drop: drop the packet.

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmExceedReplaceDscp.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmExceedReplaceDscp
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmExceedReplaceDscp.description: Specifies the DSCP value of packet when packet is in 'yellow color'. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmExceedCounterState.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmExceedCounterState
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmExceedCounterState.description: Specifies the counter state when packet is in 'yellow color'. 1. This is optional. The default is 'disabled'. 2. The resource may be limited so that the counter cannot be turned on. The limitation is project dependent. 3. counter will be cleared when the function is disabled.

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmViolateState.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmViolateState
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmViolateState.description: Specifies the action state when packet is in 'red color'. permit: permit the packet. replace-dscp: change the DSCP value of packet. drop: drop the packet.

swEgressAclMeterTrtcmViolateReplaceDscp.name: swEgressAclMeterTrtcmViolateReplaceDscp
swEgressAclMeterTrtcmViolateReplaceDscp.description: Specifies the DSCP value of the packet when packet is in 'red color'. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressAclRateTable.name: swEgressAclRateTable
swEgressAclRateTable.description: This table is used to configure the single rate two color metering function. The egress access rule must first be created before the parameters of this function can be applied. Users may set the preferred bandwidth for this rule, in Kbps; once the bandwidth has been exceeded, overflow packets will be either dropped or set for a drop precedence, depending on user configuration.

swEgressAclRateEntry.name: swEgressAclRateEntry
swEgressAclRateEntry.description: This entry displays parameters and configurations set for the single rate two color function.

swEgressAclRateProfileID.name: swEgressAclRateProfileID
swEgressAclRateProfileID.description: The ID of the egress ACL mask entry is unique in the mask list. The maximum value of this object depends on the device.

swEgressAclRateAccessID.name: swEgressAclRateAccessID
swEgressAclRateAccessID.description: The ID of the egress ACL rule entry as related to the swEgressAclRateProfileID.

swEgressAclRateRowStatus.name: swEgressAclRateRowStatus
swEgressAclRateRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swEgressAclRate.name: swEgressAclRate
swEgressAclRate.description: Specifies the committed bandwidth in Kbps for the flow. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active. NOTE: Users must set the swEgressAclRateActionForRateExceed object to activate this entry.

swEgressAclBurstSize.name: swEgressAclBurstSize
swEgressAclBurstSize.description: This specifies the burst size for the single rate two color mode. The unit is Kbytes. That is to say, 1 means 1kbytes. The set value range is 0..N, the value N is determined by project. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active. This parameter is an optional parameter. The default value is 4kbytes.

swEgressAclRateActionForRateExceed.name: swEgressAclRateActionForRateExceed
swEgressAclRateActionForRateExceed.description: Specifies the action to take for those packets exceeding the committed rate. drop-packet: drop the packet. replace-dscp: change the DSCP value of the packet. NOTE: Users must set the swEgressAclRate to activate this entry.

swEgressAclRateRemarkDscp.name: swEgressAclRateRemarkDscp
swEgressAclRateRemarkDscp.description: Mark the packet with a specified DSCP. It can be set when swEgressAclRateActionForRateExceed sets remark-dscp(3). A value of -1 indicates that this object is not active.

swEgressAclMeteringNumOfEntryInUse.name: swEgressAclMeteringNumOfEntryInUse
swEgressAclMeteringNumOfEntryInUse.description: Used to display total entries of the flow metering.
